FBIS3-44253 "drafr019_d_94013" FBIS-AFR-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Jan 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Zambia Presidential Motorcade Pelted in Western Province MB2801090994 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 0500 GMT 28 Jan 94 MB2801090994 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The United Democratic Party [UDP] has condemned the pelting of the presidential motorcade by the people of Western Province. UDP interim national chairman Mr. (Kapemba Phiri) said it was wrong for people in Mongu to behave in such a manner. He said the president should be respected regardless of which party he belonged to, and urged all leaders to discipline their members. The motorcade was pelted with stones and mangoes when President Chiluba went there to campaign for the Mongu Central by-election.
